          "Since Elon Musk took over Twitter, the national debate over free speech has narrowly focused on tech companies‚Äô social media censorship. But offline in a Texas court, a lawsuit could send an intimidating message to political candidates across the country: If you suggest billionaire donors buy political influence, you could face severe punishment."
